SIMPLE: unlock
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unlock
<hw>Un*lock"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf. AS.
<ets>unl<?/can</ets>. See 1st <er>Un-</er>, and <er>Lock</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To unfasten, as what is locked; <as>as,
to <ex>unlock</ex> a door or a chest</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To open, in general; to lay open; to undo.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Unlock</qex> your springs, and open all your shades.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Lord] <qex>unlock</qex> the spell of sin.</q> <rj><qau>J. H.
Newman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unlodge</ent>⟦br⟧
